e scene of confusion. </div><div class="t m3be8 x60 h214 y25e5 fff fs66 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">Among the mourning friends were relatives of <span class="_ _9c"></span>the family, some of</div><div class="t m3be8 x60 h214 y25e6 fff fs66 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">whom held high positions of responsibility in<span class="_ _9c"></span> Jerusalem. Among these were</div><div class="t m3be8 x60 h214 y2503 fff fs66 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">some of Christ&apos;s bitterest enemies. Christ kn<span class="_ _9c"></span>ew their purposes, and therefore</div><div class="t m3be8 x60 h214 y25e7 fff fs66 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">He did not at once make Himself known.</div><div class="t m3be8 x60 h214 y25e8 fff fs66 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The message was given to Martha so quietly t<span class="_ _9c"></span>hat others in the room did</div><div class="t m3be8 x60 h214 y25e9 fff fs66 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">not hear. Absorbed in her grief, Mary did not<span class="_ _9c"></span> hear the words. Rising at once,</div><div class="t m3be8 x60 h214 y25ea fff fs66 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">Martha went out to meet her Lord, but thinkin<span class="_ _9c"></span>g that she had gone to the</div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
